quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  94,1,Did We not expand your breast for you
  94,2,and remove your load from you
  94,3,which weighed down your back
  94,4,Did We not raise your renown high
  94,5,For truly with hardship comes ease
  94,6,truly with hardship comes ease
  94,7,"So when you have finished, work on"
  94,8,and make your Lord your goal
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,and Mount Sinai
  95,3,and this safe land
  95,4,We created man in the finest mould
  95,5,Then We reduced him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,"except for those who have iman and do right actions: they will have a wage which never fails"
  95,7,What could make you deny the Reckoning after this
  95,8,Is Allah not the Justest of Judges
  96,1,"Recite: In the Name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,created man from clots of blood
  96,3,"Recite: And your Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,He who taught by the pen
  96,5,taught man what he did not know
  96,6,No indeed! Truly man is unbridled
  96,7,seeing himself as self-sufficient
  96,8,Truly it is to your Lord that you will return
  96,9,Have you seen him who prevents
  96,10,a slave when he goes to pray
  96,11,Do you think he is rightly guided
  96,12,or commands taqwa
  96,13,Or do you see how he has denied and turned away
  96,14,Does he not know that Allah sees
  96,15,"No indeed! If he does not desist, We will grab him by the forelock"
  96,16,"a lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,Let him call his attendants
  96,18,We will call the Guards of Hell
  96,19,"No indeed! Do not obey him, but prostrate and draw near"
  97,1,Truly We sent it down on the Night of Power
  97,2,And what will convey to you what the Night of Power is
  97,3,The Night of Power is better than a thousand months
  97,4,In it the angels and the Ruh descend by their Lord´s authority with every ordinance
  97,5,It is Peace — until the coming of the dawn
  98,1,The People of the Book who are kafir and the mushrikun would not be cut off until the Clear Sign came to them
  98,2,a Messenger from Allah reciting purified texts
  98,3,containing upright precepts
  98,4,Those who were given the Book did not divide into sects until after the Clear Sign came to them
  98,5,"They were only ordered to worship Allah, making their deen sincerely His as people of pure natural belief, and to establish salat and pay zakat — that is the deen of the correct"
  98,6,"The People of the Book who are kafir and the idolaters will be in the Fire of Hell, remaining in it timelessly, for ever. They are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,But those who have iman and do right actions — they are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward is with their Lord: Gardens of Eden with rivers flowing under them, remaining in them timelessly, for ever and ever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. That is for those who fear their Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is convulsed with its quaking
  99,2,and the earth then disgorges its charges
  99,3,"and man asks, ´What is wrong with it?´"
  99,4,on that Day it will impart all its news
  99,5,because your Lord has inspired it
  99,6,That Day people will emerge segregated to see the results of their actions
  99,7,Whoever does an atom´s weight of good will see it
  99,8,Whoever does an atom´s weight of evil will see it
  100,1,By the charging horses panting hard
  100,2,striking sparks from their flashing hooves
  100,3,raiding at full gallop in the early dawn
  100,4,leaving a trailing dust-cloud in their wake
  100,5,cleaving through the middle of the foe
  100,6,truly man is ungrateful to his Lord
  100,7,and indeed he bears witness to that
  100,8,Truly he is fierce in his love of wealth